    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1051"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1051">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.501/12–1852</note>
                <head>No. 1051<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Special Assistant to the Secretary
                        for Mutual Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_BLD1" type="from"
                            >Battle</persName>) to Major General <persName type="to">George H.
                            Olmsted</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-12-18">December 18,
                            1952</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Request Involving Reimbursable Military Assistance Under Section 408(e) of
                        the MDAA, as Amended.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Reference is made to copies of cable number 2217 dated June 13, 1952 from the
                    American Embassy in Cairo<note n="1" xml:id="d1051fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    containing an official request from the Egyptian Government for police and
                    military equipment as shown in the attached list,<note n="1" target="d1051fn1"
                        >Not printed.</note> Egypt Case No. 3.</p>
                <p>This equipment was originally intended for the use of Egyptian police divisions
                    but an amendment to the existing agreement now permits its use by the Egyptian
                    Army.</p>
                <p>The Department of State approves, from an economic and political viewpoint, the
                    meeting of this request under the provisions of Section 408(e) of the Mutual
                    Defense Assistance Act of 1949, as amended. The foregoing approval is subject to
                    clearance with respect to any patent and proprietary rights, if such rights are
                    involved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">L. D. Battle</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
